cle">

 =20
      <h2>
      <a href=3D"https://ottheory.com/therapy-model/occupation-centred-asse=
ssment-children-ocac-framework" rel=3D"bookmark"><span class=3D"field field=
--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Occupation-Centred Ass=
essment with Children (OCAC) framework </span>
</a>
    </h2>
   =20

 =20
  <div>
    <div class=3D"clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--typ=
e-text-with-summary field--label-hidden">
      <ul class=3D"links field__items">
              <li><p>The Occupation-Centred Assessment with Children (OCAC)=
 framework is a top-down, family-centered, ad ecological assessment approac=
h that provides a holistic view of children and their occupational performa=
nce within their naturalistic contexts. OCAC focuses on occupational perfor=
mance issues most relevant and important to a child and his/her family. The=
se may include leisure/play, productivity/school, self-care/activities of d=
aily living, as well as time use, roles, habits, identity, and activity pat=
terns.</p></li>
        </ul>
</div>

  <div class=3D"node__links">
